{
  "texts": [
    "Challenge 6 How to Ensure the Validity of LLM Output?Although LLM cannot guarantee 100% accuracy on the task results, certain database tasks require strict constraints (e.g., the output of query rewrite must be a semantically equivalent query and the query must be executable on the database).",
    "It is essential to ensure that all invalid outputs are detected or avoided.Vision 6 We propose to adopt a hybrid method to ensure the validity of model output.",
    "First, we should design special training set so that LLM can maximize the possibility of generating valid outputs (e.g., queries that satisfy the SQL syntax).",
    "Second, for relatively simple cases, we adopt a nonlearned checking layer to validate the output (e.g., using an SMT solver for simple SPJ queries [43]).",
    "For more complex cases, we adopt a learned checking layer (e.g., a binary classifier) to validate the output."
  ]
}